<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MinGW specific. Remove default manifests (with language zero) if there are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// other manifests present, and report an error if there are more than one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="256"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// manifest with a non-zero language code.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="257"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GCC has the concept of a default manifest resource object, which gets</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="258"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// linked in implicitly if present. This default manifest has got language</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// id zero, and should be dropped silently if there&#39;s another manifest present.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the user resources surprisignly had a manifest with language id zero,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we should also ignore the duplicate default manifest.</span></CodeLine>
